18b8d8b0-ed96-4200-97c3-ccef66fb980f.Text:
The Bladedancer faces a side of their choice and immediately ends their turn. Until the beginning of the Bladedancer's next turn, they can {g|Encyclopedia:DodgeGlossary}dodge{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:AreaOfEffect}area attacks{/g} without moving, are immune to all types of forced movement, gain +20% {g|Encyclopedia:Parry}parry{/g} against attacks from that side, and can now parry attacks made against adjacent allies. While under the effect of <b>Veil of Blades</b>, the Bladedancer can even parry ranged attacks (except ranged area attacks) made from that side. The chance to parry a ranged attack is calculated as if it were a {g|Encyclopedia:MeleeAttacksGlossary}melee attack{/g}, where the attacker's {g|Encyclopedia:WarhammerWeaponSkill}Weapon Skill{/g} is equal to the {g|Encyclopedia:HitSequenceGlossary}hit chance{/g} of the attack. If an attack is parried in this way, it can be redirected toward one of the enemies on the selected side. The chance of redirection is equal to half of the Bladedancer's parry chance against this attack.
The Bladedancer will also gain +2 charges of {g|f:c3d6e29e74e440a79cb243e4e93e0501}Death From Above{/g}
! This {g|Encyclopedia:Ability}ability{/g} can only be used with a sword equipped.
